(73, 2, 'KATHMANDU TOUR  03 DAYS/02 NIGHTS', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TENTATIVE ITINERARY: NO: 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 01: Arrival / Kathmandu&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, Kathmandu and transfer to hotel. Overnight at Hotel of your choice, Kathmandu.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 02: Kathmandu sightseeing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, leave for sightseeing tour to Kathmandu valley covering Swayambhunath Stupa, Pashupatinath Temple, Boudhnath. Evening - free on your own. Overnight at Hotel of your choice, Kathmandu.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 03: Final Departure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, free until transfer to Tribhuvan International Airport for final departure.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TOUR END&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'upload/d2b6c1ff99.jpg', 'Mona', 'nepal tour from bangladesg,', '2018-06-12 11:31:01', 9),
(74, 2, 'KATHMANDU &amp; NAGARKOT TOUR 03 DAYS / 02 NIGHTS', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TENTATIVE ITINERARY: NO:2 (ONLY BY PRIVATE CAR POSSIBLE)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 01: Arrival / Kathmandu&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, Kathmandu and transfer to hotel. Overnight at Hotel Kathmandu.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 02: Kathmandu sightseeing &amp;amp; drive to Nagarkot&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, check out form hotel and leave for sightseeing tour to Kathmandu valley covering Swayambhunath Stupa, Pashupatinath Temple and Patan Durbar Square. Continue drive to Nagarkot. Reach Nagarkot and check in to hotel. Evening &amp;ndash; enjoy the sunset view from hotel premises. Overnight at Hotel&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Nagarkot.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 03: Final Departure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, check out form hotel and leave for Tribhuvan International Airport for final departure.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TOUR END&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'upload/85257ae3b9.jpg', 'Mona', 'nepal tour from bangladesg,', '2018-06-12 11:31:58', 9),
(75, 2, 'KATHMANDU - POKHARA TOUR 04 DAYS/03 NIGHTS', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TENTATIVE ITINERARY:NO:3 (ONLY BY PRIVATE CAR POSSIBLE)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 01: Arrival / Kathmandu&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, Kathmandu and transfer to hotel. Overnight at Kathmandu&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 02: Drive to Pokhara&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, check out from hotel and drive to Pokhara. Pokhara is around 210 km, 6-7 hrs drive, from Kathmandu. Reach Pokhara and check in to hotel. Visit Taal Barahi Temple with 1 hour boating on Phewa Lake Overnight at Hotel, Pokhara&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 03: Pokhara sightseeing &amp;amp; Drive back to Kathmandu&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, leave for sightseeing tour to Pokhara city covering Bindyabashini Temple, Mahendra Cave, Seti Gorge, Davis Fall and after lunch&amp;nbsp; check out from hotel and drive back to Kathmandu. Reach Kathmandu and check in to hotel. Overnight at Hotel Kathmandu&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 04:&amp;nbsp; Kathmandu sightseeing &amp;amp; Final Departure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast visit half day sightseeing of Pashupati, Swyambhunath &amp;amp; Boudhanath, Rani Pokhri, Durbar Mesume etc &amp;amp;&amp;nbsp; transfer to Tribhuvan International Airport for final departure.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TOUR END&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'upload/d6453a89aa.jpg', 'Mona', 'nepal tour from bangladesg,', '2018-06-12 11:33:31', 9),
(76, 2, 'NAGARKOT-KATHMANDU - POKHARA TOUR 04 DAYS/03 NIGHTS', '<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">TENTATIVE ITINERARY:NO:4 (ONLY BY PRIVATE CAR POSSIBLE).</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 01: Arrival / Kathmandu&nbsp; &amp; Transfer to Nagarkot. ( 40 km/1 Hours) </strong></p>\r\n<p>Arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, Kathmandu and transfer to hotel. Overnight at Nagarkot.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: Drive to Pokhara</strong></p>\r\n<p>Early morning visit Sun rise point. After breakfast, check out from hotel and drive to Pokhara. Pokhara is around 200 km, 6-7 hrs drive, from Kathmandu. Reach Pokhara and check in to hotel. Overnight at Hotel, Pokhara</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: Pokhara sightseeing &amp; Drive back to Kathmandu</strong></p>\r\n<p>After breakfast, leave for sightseeing tour to Pokhara city covering Bindyabashini Temple, Mahendra Cave, Seti Gorge, Davis Fall and after lunch&nbsp; check out from hotel and drive back to Kathmandu. Reach Kathmandu and check in to hotel. Overnight at Hotel Kathmandu</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 04:&nbsp; Kathmandu sightseeing &amp; Final Departure</strong></p>\r\n<p>After breakfast visit half day sightseeing of Pashupati, Swyambhunath &amp; Boudhanath, Rani Pokhri, Durbar Mesume etc &amp;&nbsp; transfer to Tribhuvan International Airport for final departure.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">TOUR END</span></strong></p>', 'upload/1d8461db1c.jpg', 'Mona', 'nepal tour from bangladesg,', '2018-06-12 11:34:01', 9),
(77, 2, 'KATHMANDU - POKHARA TOUR 05 DAYS/04 NIGHTS', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TENTATIVE ITINERARY:NO:5 ( By Bus/Private car)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 01: Arrival/Kathmandu&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, Kathmandu and transfer to hotel. Overnight at Kathmandu.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 02: Drive to Pokhara&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, check out from hotel and drive to Pokhara. Pokhara is around 200 km, 6-7 hrs drive, from Kathmandu. Reach Pokhara and check in to hotel. Overnight at Hotel, Pokhara.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 03: Pokhara sightseeing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, leave for sightseeing tour to Pokhara city covering Bindyabashini Temple, Mahendra Cave, Seti Gorge, Davis Fall and Taal Barahi Temple with 1 hour boating on Phewa Lake. Overnight at Hotel, Pokhara.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 04: Drive back to Kathmandu&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, check out from hotel and drive back to Kathmandu. Reach Kathmandu and check in to hotel. Evening - free on your own at Thamel area. Overnight at Hotel Kathmandu.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 05: &amp;nbsp;Kathmandu sightseeing &amp;amp; Final Departure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;After breakfast visit half day sightseeing of Pashupati, Swyambhunath &amp;amp; Boudhanath, Rani Pokhri, Durbar Mesume etc &amp;amp; &amp;nbsp;transfer to Tribhuvan International Airport for final departure.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;TOUR END&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'upload/187bf76669.jpg', 'Mona', 'nepal tour from bangladesg,', '2018-06-12 11:34:27', 9),
(78, 6, '05 Days 04 Nights Cairo', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;DAY 1&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; CAIRO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Arrival in Cairo international airport, Meet &amp;amp; Assist at the airport and After going through Immigration, Baggage Claim and Customs, Transfer to the hotel dinner And Overnight.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;DAY 2&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;FULL DAY CAIRO TOUR &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;HIGHLIGHTS OF THE DAY&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE PYRAMIDS OF GIZA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Pyramids of Choeps, Chepren and Mycerious.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The great pyramids are the only ones surviving of the seven wonders of the ancient world. They are Egypt\'s most visited monuments and among the worlds greatest tourist attractions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;The Ancient Egyptians built the pyramids as tombs to preserve the bodies of their dead kings, especially that they believed in resurrection and immortality, The Pyramids of Giza lie at the western edge of Greater Cairo, about 10 kms from downtown, and comprise: &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The Great Pyramid&lt;br /&gt; The most famous structure in the world and the only surviving of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World. It was built by King Khufu (Cheops) of the IV Dynasty around 2650 BC. lts height now is 137 m (original height: 146 m). Almost 2.5 million blocks of stone were put into building this pyramid. All this, however, dwindles when compared to the precision and astounding ability of the ancient Egyptian in building this pyramid. Close to the eastern flank of the Pyramid of Khufu lie three small pyramids dedicated either to his wives or family members.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Second Pyramid&lt;br /&gt; Built by Khafre (Chephren), south-west of his father\'s (Khufu\'s) pyramid though lower in height: 136 m. It still retains, on some of its upper parts, the remains of the limestone that had once covered it all. At the base, it measures 215.5 m square. lts interior is simple, with two entrances on the north side. The visitor can also still see the remains of Khafre\'s mortuary temple, the Temple of the Valley, and rising causeway. These temples witnessed the religious rites during the embalming of the body. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The Third Pyramid&lt;br /&gt; Built by Menkaure (Mycerinus), south-west of the Great and Second Pyramids. It is much smaller than either one (62 m high). It is distinguished by the fact that the lower part of its sides still retain their granite slab coverings.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE SPHINX&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;On the way to the Temple of the Valley, lies the large statue of the Sphinx. The Sphinx is carved from a single piece of stone. &amp;nbsp;One of most famous monuments in the world, it is indeed a legendary statue for it has the body of lion and the face of a man. lt is 70 m long and 20 m high. The face of the Sphinx closely resembles that of King Kephren.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;THE PERFUMERY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Since time immemorial the Egyptians have been extracting essential oils for essences. Here you have a chance to experience the aromas like, \'The secrets of the desert,\' \'The lotus\' and all popular international designer perfumes and colognes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;THE PAPYRUS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The papyrus was first made in ancient Egypt- learn how to manufacture this paper using papyrus reeds. And you have an opportunity to buy some hand painted papyrus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Lunch at local restaurant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&amp;middot; &lt;strong&gt;EGYPTIAN MUSEUM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Called the museum of the Egyptian antiquities, it is one of the greatest museums you will ever see, housing an unrivalled collection of antiquities reaching back 5000years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;DAY 3&amp;nbsp;CAIRO-ALEXANDRIA-CAIRO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast at the hotel. Transfer to Alexandria by road (2.5 hrs approx)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Highlights of the day:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;middot; &lt;strong&gt;THE &amp;nbsp; CATACOMBS OF KOM EL SHOUKAFA&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Kom El Shoukafa is an underground wonder &amp;nbsp; world of ornate carvings and paintings and a mixture of Roman and Egyptian designs. It is the largest Roman Funerary complex in Egypt. And dates from the second century A.D. This warren of tombs, on three levels, also contains the Triclinium, where relatives used to sit on stone benches to feast the dead, and a central tomb with reliefs of bearded serpents. Inside are 2nd century A.D. statues of Sobek and Anubis wearing roman armor.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;middot; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;CITADEL OF FORT QAITBEY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;This citadel is the further most edifices on the harbors arm. The fort is on the original site of the Pharos, Alexandria&amp;rsquo;s ancient lighthouse, built in 279 BC to a height of 12 meters and topped with the statue of Poseidon. Although Pharos was restored at various times it had finally crumbled by the time the original fort was built here, in the 1480&amp;rsquo;s. This magnificent structure houses Fort Qait Beys naval museum.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;middot; &lt;strong&gt;THE ROMAN THEATER&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Discovered in 1964, after 30 years of excavation, this well preserved ancient Roman Theatre with the marble seats, galleries and sections of mosaic flooring, was probably a roofed theatre used for musical performances and based on the inscriptions carved on the seats, wrestling contests. The theatre had a capacity of 700 to 800 seats and in Ptolemaic times it was park of Pan, a pleasure garden surrounded by Roman villas and baths.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Return to Cairo. Evening at leisure&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;DAY 4.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;FULL DAY CAIRO TOUR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Breakfast at the hotel. Proceed to the full day tour for the day&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;HIGHLIGHTS OF THE DAY&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;COPTIC CAIRO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE HANGING CHURCH (AL MUALLAQA)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The hanging church was built in the 4&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century over southern gate of the fortress of Babylon .Dedicated to Virgin Mary, its treasures includes a 14 th century wall painting of the Nativity.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CHURCH OF&amp;nbsp;ST.SERGIUS (ABU SERGA)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A 5 th century basilica built over crypt where the Holy Family is believed to have stayed during their flight into Egypt.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CHURCH OF ST.MERCURIUS (ABU SEFEIN)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;It boasts a unique collection of Coptic art including 175 icons that depict scenes from the old and new testaments, wall paintings, etching and stained glass.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GREEK ORTHODOX CHURCH OF MARI GIRGIS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Built on one of the towers of Babylon Fortress, this basilica is round in structure with domed roof.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Lunch at local restaurant.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Return to the hotel for dinner&amp;nbsp;and overnight.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pharaonic Village &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Take a step back in time; about three thousand years back, to be exact. Just a few miles from the center of Cairo is a time machine waiting to take you on a fantastic journey to the days of the Pharaohs, a time brought to life by an incredible group of actors and actresses, faithful and exact reproductions of buildings, clothing, and lifestyles At the pharaonick Village, visitors sail on comfortable motorized barges down a network of canals and view incredibly accurate &lt;em&gt;tableaux&lt;/em&gt; of the recreation of ancient Egyptian life. Over a hundred actors and actresses perform all the daily activities and arts of the ancient Egyptians, including agriculture, pottery, sculpture, weaving, and much more. Everyone that would have existed in an ancient Egyptian city is here in the modern recreation, from pharaohs to fishermen, from potters to priests. Because of this attention to detail, the pharaonick Village is more than education and entertainment; it is a vital resource in the preservation of our knowledge of the ancient world.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In the evening there is &lt;strong&gt;Nile cruise Dinner&lt;/strong&gt;, which lasts for 2 hours, sailing on the Nile with Folkloric Shows and Belly Dancers. At the end of this cruise you will be driven back to your hotel&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;DAY 5 .&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Departure &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Your final day starts with breakfast at the hotel followed by check-out. You will then be transferred to the airport for your final departure.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;End of Program&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Not Included:&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;- Visa Entry for Egypt. &lt;br /&gt; - International Flights &lt;br /&gt; - Personal items. &lt;br /&gt; - Tipping. &lt;br /&gt; - Any other items not mentioned. &lt;br /&gt; - Any Optional tours.&lt;br /&gt; - Any meals not stated on the itinerary.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 'upload/ed7508e784.jpg', 'Sabbir Ahmed', 'Egypt tour from bangladesh', '2018-06-12 11:36:58', 5),
(79, 6, '8 Days / 7 Nights 3 Nights Cairo 4 Nights Sharm El_Sheikh', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 1 : &amp;nbsp;Cairo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Arrival to Cairo airport, our representative will assist you through passport control formalities, luggage identification &amp;amp; portage will greet you. From the airport you will be transferred by a private A/C car to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 2: Cairo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast. Start your tour visiting the Great Pyramids - Cheops, Chephren &amp;amp; Mykerions. Cheops is the most colossal ever built. Next is a close-up look at Sphinx - a huge funeral complex guarded by the legendary lion body with the face of king Chephren. Then continue to Khan El Khalili Bazaars. Shops in this district are legendary for fine border brassware, copper, perfumes, leather, silver, gold, antiques &amp;hellip;etc.Followed by Lunch .At the end of the day we will transfer you back to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 3 : Sharm El Shiekh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast, Transfer By Road To Sharm Arrival, meet &amp;amp; assist by our local representatives and transfer to the hotel. At Night Enjoy Sharm &lt;strong&gt;Disco&lt;/strong&gt; And Night In Sharm&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Overnight in Sharm.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 4: Sharm El Shiekh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast. Free Day Or &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;( Optional Tour )&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;start your Full Day Tour: Boat trip to Tiran Island with Lunch :Enjoy sun bathing on the sun deck, snorkeling at the three different spots on the reef and swim with a variety of different colored fishes, on a fantastic day of fun and sun. Soft drinks and mineral waters are available throughout the day, Followed by lunch in the afternoon. At the end transfer you back to your Hotel in Sharm.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 5: Sharm El Shiekh&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast .In Hotel . Free Day Or &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;( Optional Tour )&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Discover Sharm Desert with&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; Ultimate Desert Experience Quad Bike, Camel ride, Bedouin dinner,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;This trip has everything - spectacular Desert scenery, a taste of Bedouin culture and a quad bike and camel ride to boot and it all begins in the afternoon. Ride through beautiful desert terrain to a traditional tented Bedouin camp. Once you have caught your breath, it\'s then time to clamber onto a camel and take a swaying ride over the sand. After that maybe have a puff on a shisha pipe and sip some Bedouin tea before sitting down to a BBQ dinner. Come dusk, your trip is rounded off with a show. Simply brilliant! We will pick you up from your hotel in our bus and drive you to our Falcon center quad bike ,sand buggy &amp;nbsp;(approx. 20 minutes) away. After a brief guide on how to use the quad bike safely, we will then race off for your &quot;Ultimate Desert Experience&quot;, one we hope you will always remember!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 6: Sharm El Shiekh&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast. Free day&amp;nbsp; , Over Night .&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 7: Sharm / Cairo &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast. Departure by Road To Cairo , arrive Cairo Transfer To Hotel ,&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Day 8: Departure &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Breakfast. Departure To Airport For Your Final Flight Home .&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Program includes:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;- 3 Nights hotel accommodation in Cairo 5 Stars on bed and breakfast basis. &lt;br /&gt; - 4 Nights hotel accommodation in Sharm El Sheikh &amp;nbsp;5 Stars on All inclusive basis. &lt;br /&gt; - 1 Full day tour in Cairo visiting the Pyramids, Sphinx &amp;amp; Khan El Khalili. &lt;br /&gt; - All transfers in Cairo and Sharm El Sheikh. &lt;br /&gt; - Multilingual expert Egyptologist guide. &lt;br /&gt; - All your tours and excursions are with A/C bus. &lt;br /&gt; - The service of meet and assist at all your destinations. &lt;br /&gt; - All your visits include entrance fees. &lt;br /&gt; - Our prices include all taxes and services&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Not Included:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; - Personal items. &lt;br /&gt; - Tipping. &lt;br /&gt; - Any other items not mentioned. &lt;br /&gt; - Any meals not stated on the itinerary&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;table style=&quot;width: 642px;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;\r\n&lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;100&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;Hotels Category&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;120&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;Hotel In Cairo&lt;